### Blockquote

The <blockquote> tag specifies a section that is quoted from another source. Browsers usually indent <blockquote> elements. 
You can create a blockquote using any element by adding .quote class to that element. You can change the style of the 
blockquote using default colors .success, .info, .warning, .danger, just make sure that any blackquote you want to 
use default colors on has a .quote class applied to.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Blockquote Start -->
<blockquote>
  <p>
    There is enough in the world for everyone's need, but not for everyone's greed.
  </p>
  <cite>Frank Buchman</cite>
</blockquote>
<!-- Blockquote End -->

<!-- Blockquote Success Start -->
<blockquote class="quote success">
  <p>
    Coming together is a beginning; keeping together is progress; 
    working together is success.
  </p>
  <cite>Henry Ford</cite>
</blockquote>
<!-- Blockquote Success End -->
```

Using .reverse class, we can flip / reverse blockquotes. See example below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Blockquote Start -->
<blockquote class="quote info reverse">
  <p>
    There is enough in the world for everyone's need, but not for everyone's greed.
  </p>
  <cite>Frank Buchman</cite>
</blockquote>
<!-- Blockquote End -->
```

### Drop Cap

A drop cap is a means to stylize a paragraph and to add a little splash and flavor to a page. 
You can create a drop cap by adding .dropcap class to a paragraph and wrapping the first letter 
of that paragraph inside a <span> tag with a .dp class for basic drop cap or .dp-bg class for 
background drop cap. See examples below.

##### html
----------

```
<!-- Default Drop Cap Start -->
<p class="dropcap">
  <span class="dp">O</span>ver 100,000 people are estimated to have died since the 
  violence began, and more than two million have fled over the borders as refugees into 
  Lebanon, Turkey, Jordan and Iraq. A million of these refugees are children. Stories 
  emerged of children being detained, tortured by, and even used as human shields by the 
  security forces. In August 2013 chemical weapons were allegedly used against civilians.
</p>
<!-- Default Drop Cap End -->

<!-- Background Drop Cap Start -->
<p class="dropcap">
  <span class="dp-bg blue">O</span>ver 100,000 people are estimated to have died since the 
  violence began, and more than two million have fled over the borders as refugees into 
  Lebanon, Turkey, Jordan and Iraq. A million of these refugees are children. Stories 
  emerged of children being detained, tortured by, and even used as human shields by the 
  security forces. In August 2013 chemical weapons were allegedly used against civilians.
</p>
<!-- Background Drop Cap End -->
```









